stylometry: An advantage of simulation models is that it imitates real life solution. It takes in account uncertainty in input variables getting random and various values. It can show an entire distribution of results, not just a single solution that other solutions may give, and different values for the uncertain quantities that are involved. It shows how sensitive an operating system is to change. It answers what-if questions and allows to see results without actually making a physical model. An example is implementing a new car into the market and trying to simulate the profit fro ten years. It can consider things like demand, cost of developing, and can predict using @risk the NPV of the car.
